1. Explain about Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ðŸ‘‰ Power Apps is a Microsoft low-code/no-code platform, that allows we can quickly build custom business applications without need any coding skills.
ðŸ‘‰ It supports creating an apps with drag-and-drop controls, connecting to different data sources like SharePoint, Dataverse, and more.

ðŸ‘‰ Power Apps supports building an apps mainly two types:
1. Canvas Apps.
2. Model-Driven Apps.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ðŸ”¹ Key features of Power Apps (based on my experience):
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
1. Low-code development             ---> I build apps quickly using drag-and-drop conrols without need any coding skills.
2. Canvas and Model-Driven apps     ---> I choose based on UI needs or data focus.
3. Multiple data connections        ---> I connect apps easily to SharePoint, Dataverse, SQL, Excel, etc.
4. Integration with PowerAutomate   ---> I automate workflows from inside the app itself.
5. Security and permissions         ---> I manage user access through Dataverse security roles.
6. Responsive design                ---> Especially with Model-Driven apps, it adjusts automatically for mobile and Desktop.
7. Reusable components              ---> I create custom components to maintain consistency across apps.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Difference between Canvas App and Model-Driven App?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ðŸ‘‰ Canvas App provides a blank canvas where i can build fully customized UI by dragging and dropping controls â€” like galleries, forms, buttons and media components.
ðŸ‘‰ One of the key advantages is more flexibility.
ðŸ‘‰ I can integrate my apps to multiple data sources like SharePoint or Dataverse depending on the requirement.

ðŸ‘‰ In Model-Driven Apps, the design is based on data structure â€” like forms, views, charts and dashboards. 
   â€” so that layout is automatically generated by Power Apps.
ðŸ‘‰ I prefer Model-Driven Apps for complex business processes where we already have structured data in Dataverse, like (eg, Customer Service apps). 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. Variables and types of Variables in power apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ðŸ‘‰ Variables are mainly used to store temporarily data. 
ðŸ‘‰ This data can any type, such as numbers, strings, or booleans, depending on the situation.

ðŸ”¹ Types of Variables:
1ï¸âƒ£ Context Variables are Scoped only to the current screen.
ðŸ’› Syntax: UpdateContext({ VariableName: Value }) || Example: UpdateContext({ varName: "Manoj" })  

2ï¸âƒ£ Global variables are accessible throughout the entire app across all screens.
ðŸ’› Syntax: Set( VariableName, Value ) || Example: Set(varCountry, "India") 

Example:
ðŸ‘‰ In my project, I used a Global variable to store logged-in user role, a Context variable to open and close popups, 
    and a Collection to cache SharePoint list data for faster performance.
