16. How do you create a Responsive Design in Power Apps?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ðŸ‘‰ Responsive design means building apps that automatically adapt their layout and controls to fit any screen size,
    â€” whether it's desktop, tablet, or mobile.
ðŸ‘‰ To create a responsive Design, I use layout controls like vertical or horizontal containers depending on the appâ€™s structure.
ðŸ‘‰ These containers automatically arrange the elements inside them based on the screen size.
ðŸ‘‰ Instead of fixing each controlâ€™s size and position, I use formulas to set width and height.

For Example:
ðŸ‘‰ Uisng relative properities like "parent.width and parent.height", 
   â€” that controls automatically adjust their sizes and positions dynamically.
