17. What are the Role-Based Security in Power Apps. How do you manage them?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ðŸ‘‰ Role-Based Security in Power Apps and Dataverse controls what users can see and do based on their assigned roles â€” such as Admin, Manager, or Employee.
ðŸ‘‰ In Dataverse, I assign security roles directly to users or teams depending on their responsibilities.
ðŸ‘‰ Each role defines specific permissions â€” like Read, Write, create or Delete â€” across tables, forms, apps, or even specific records.

Example:
ðŸ‘‰ In my recent project, Managers had access to update employee data, while Employees could only view their own profile.
