20. Difference between configuration and customization?

EXPLAIN IN ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ðŸ‘‰ Configuration means using built-in settings to make the system work how you want, without any coding. 
-> Example: Changing app themes, modifying forms, enabling features, adding fields, or setting security roles. 

ðŸ‘‰ Customization means writing code or building new features to change how the system works. 
-> Example: Creating custom connectors, writing Power Automate flows, or building custom controls.    

ðŸ‘‰ So, configuration is easier and faster, and customization is for when you need something more advanced.







